From 70f428c60c7a8c014546d688a5302d30eb62f4a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 11:51:33 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: live-tick output tokens + soft re-render during
 streaming
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three streaming-UX fixes:

1. Output-token live tick. Anthropic only sends authoritative
   output_tokens once, in the final message_delta. Until then,
   estimate from accumulatedText.length / 4 (Anthropic's rough
   chars-per-token) on every text delta and surface that as
   liveUsage.outputTokens. The number now climbs while the
   model is still writing instead of jumping from 0 to N at
   the end.

2. Soft re-render path. The pane's onUpdate distinguishes
   chapter-count changes (structural — needs full re-layout)
   from usage-only ticks (cosmetic — just touch the
   subheading text node). Soft updates no longer rebuild the
   storyboard DOM, so clicks, hover, and focus survive token
   ticks. Structural updates capture and restore the
   storyboard scroller's scroll position so adding a new
   node doesn't yank the user's view back to the top-left.

3. Streaming spinner. New '.krt-pr-streaming-badge' chip in
   both Tour and Storyboard headers. Visible (animated) while
   tourStreaming === true, hidden once the stream completes.
   refreshTourSubheading and refreshStoryboardSubheading both
   call refreshStreamingBadges so the chip stays in sync with
   every soft update.

Token-emit calls inside TourGenerator are also throttled to
~150ms so the channel doesn't spam the renderer with one
event per text delta when only the count is changing.
